						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone lying in Hāḷavaḍḍaragēri.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vijayāditya—(Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This inscription refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vijayāditya Satyāśraya</hi> and records the death of a hero (name lost). As it is very badly damaged and worn out, its purport cannot be made out. The characters of the record are of the <hi rend="bold">8th century A.D.</hi> The place-name <hi rend="bold">Beḷgalli</hi> may be noted. A certain Sirisāgara is mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
